A Nigerian woman who got married in 2002 but could not conceive for 18 years, has died, just three days after welcoming a set of twins.<img src="https://i1.wp.com/instablog9ja.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instablog9ja_20200731_17.jpg?resize=1024%2C1024" />Mrs Chika Anthonia Voghor, welcomed a boy and a girl via a caesarean section on Monday, June 22, 2020 but sadly passed away three days after, due to internal bleeding. The deceased’s sister, Mrs. Nwamuruamu Akachukwu Scholastica, who spoke with Nigerian Tribune said, “She gave birth on Monday. On Tuesday, she was happy rejoicing, and full of life. In fact, the news was an exciting one to everyone that knew her.” Unfortunately, she became pale that Tuesday evening, and a doctor who was called confirmed she had internal bleeding. She was subsequently rushed to the hospital where she later died. “She died at exactly 5:30a.m in my presence. I couldn’t even look at the children. I was devastated,” Akachukwu added. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.